'''ADD Grup''', is a developer and manufacturer of [[smart metering]] solutions.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://newsmaker.md/rus/novosti/aleksey-lazarev-na-samom-dele-my-gorazdo-luchshe-ih-umnee-my-golodnye-a-oni-sytye-10667 |title=Алексей Лазарев: "На самом деле мы гораздо лучше их, умнее. Мы голодные, а они сытые" |publisher=NewsMaker}}</ref> The company is based in [[Chișinău]], Moldova.
The company’s primary product is the ADDAX IMS system for electricity metering, multi-utility metering and streetlight management. The system offers a suite of interconnected hardware and software tools, including [[electricity meter]]s, communication endpoints, network infrastructure and data management applications.<ref>{{cite web|title=ADDAX IMS - Part of Intracom Telecom lowest bid for HEDNO smart metering project in Greece|url=https://www.metering.com/industry-sectors/smart-meters/addax-ims-part-intracom-telecom-lowest-bid-hedno-smart-metering-project-greece/|website=Metering.com}}</ref> Supported functionalities include [[Electricity meter|ToU metering]], load profile, [[load control]], demand response, [[fraud detection]], imbalance control and prepayment.<ref>{{cite web|title=ADD GRUP Case Study|url=http://www.analog.com/en/education/education-library/customer-success-stories-add-grup.html|website=Analog Devices|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Prague Electric Network continues installation of ADDAX PRIME-based smart metering|url=https://www.metering.com/regional-news/europe-uk/prague-electric-network-continues-installation-of-addax-prime-based-smart-metering/|website=Metering.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=EVN Macedonia to deploy 18 000 ADDAX meters|url=http://www.pennenergy.com/articles/pennenergy/2014/09/advanced-metering-evn-macedonia-to-deploy-18-000-addax-meters.html|website=PennEnergy}}</ref>
== History== ADD Grup was originally known as ADD, established in 1992.
In 2014, ADD Grup launched the Universal Platform that "allows to change the technology on basis of which smart meters and routers operate" and this was exhibited through a project in [[Latvia]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.metering.com/deal-watch-add-grup-to-deploy-ami-in-latvia/ |title=ADD GRUP wins contract for AMI system in Latvia |publisher=Metering.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.sadalestikls.lv/eng/aktualitates/preses_relizes/521-nearly-70000-customers-already-use-smart-electricity-meters |title=Nearly 70,000 customers already use smart electricity meters |publisher=AS "Sadales tīkls"}}</ref>
As of 2016, the company has supplied over 5 million smart meters worldwide.<ref>{{cite web|title=ADD GRUP awarded contract to provide 11,040 meters to Poland|url=https://www.metering.com/regional-news/europe-uk/add-grup-poland/|website=Metering.com}}</ref>
In 2017, ADD Grup was chosen by the representatives of the [[European Council]] as a successful hi-tech company for a video campaign to promote success stories of companies exporting from [[Moldova]] to the [[European Union]].<ref>{{cite web|title=European Union market is key for the Moldovan economy - EEAS - European External Action Service|url=https://eeas.europa.eu/delegations/moldova/28159/press-release-european-union-market-key-moldovan-economy_en|website=European Commission|language=en}}</ref>
